It was January of 2010 when i first met Uncle Chucc. He was hosting a jam session at this place called Cozy’s in the valley. Without any co-sign from another musician and no prior knowledge of me, he gave my a shot and let me sit in that night. From that point forward, i would play in his bands whether it was a church or a nightclub. During that time i would have not only have the opportunity to hone in on my craft, i would get to cross paths and sometimes play with musicians i looked up to. The experience and lessons i would gain from playing with him would be invaluable. This is the only picture i could find of that time in my life playing alongside him. Thank you for giving me a chance. Thank you for being blunt with me when i needed advice and motivation. Thank you for giving me an opportunity to grow. Thank you for being a friend. I wish I could tell you all this in person. Rest in heaven, bro. Til next time @iamunclechucc . 🕊️🕊️🕊️🙏🏼🙏🏼🙏🏼#thelaces #thezionmessengers
